description:
12 page Bonnie Taylor story "Flight 101 -- to Heartbreak!"

Stewardess Bonnie Taylor has to face an old boyfriend when he's traveling to Paris with his new girlfriend on her flight.

description:
Meet Bonnie Taylor the lovely airline stewardess who flies in and out of romantic adventures!

Note: cover art taken from splash page of first story in this issue

12 page Bonnie Taylor story "Another Face -- Another Love!"

Bonnie meets a sad serviceman on a flight to Paris and does her best to cheer him up, but in the end he goes back to his girlfriend.

1 page Romance in Fashion illustration

Fashions submitted by B. Kennedy; Jan Baker

8 page story "Love Is Only a Word on a Typewriter!"

Penny helps Steve, a struggling writer, but he already has a fiancee. She tries to forget her feelings by dating Tom, but fortunately Steve realizes that it's Penny he really loves and comes back to her.

1 page Romance in Fashion illustration

another fashion page

2 page Laura Penn... Your Romance Reporter letters page "I have a problem that is troubling me a lot..."

Typeset relationship advice article

8 page story "Wait for My Love"

David and Mary are childhood sweethearts separated when she and her parents move away. David never forgets her, but years later when they meet again, Mary has forgotten him.
name: "Another Face -- Another Love!"

description:
12 page Bonnie Taylor story "Too Late for Love!"

SynopsisBonnie meets a stewardess in Holland who resembles her, who tells her of a man she met briefly when she was a nurse in the Korean War. Bonnie later discovers that the mysterious man is the same one she recently saw in London who seemed to recognize her, and she helps the two find each other again.
name: Too Late For Love

description: July 1964
name: No Home for My heart

description:
12 page Bonnie Taylor story "Dreams Don't Count!"

When Bonnie's roommate Lori is feared dead in a plane crash, Bonnie comforts Lori's boyfriend Tod and falls in love with him herself, but has to let him go when Lori is found safe.
name: Dreams Don't Count!

description:
15 page Bonnie Taylor story "His Other Love!"

SynopsisBonnie meets a handsome stranger in France who mistakes her for a girl he loved and lost during WW II.
15 page Bonnie Taylor story "Last Kiss -- First Heartache!" - Bonnie is on her way to Venice to reunite with an actor she met there briefly, but he fails to show up for their planned rendezvous.
name: Last Kiss First Heartache

description:
15 page Bonnie Taylor story "A Ticket to Romance!"

Bonnie's fellow stewardess Angie thinks that Bonnie is much luckier at love, but Bonnie has many unhappy stories to tell. When they arrive in Paris they go to a masquerade ball, where the man that Bonnie has her eye on ends up with Angie. Bonnie flees the party, but a handsome stranger comforts her.
name: "A Ticket to Romance!"

description:
James Jensen, the soldier who became a mystic continues his journey which takes him beyond the limits of the physical world into Limbo. There he encounters another like him whose saga has been told in legends. But the problem with legends is that they are not always true.

Eastern mystic James Jensen, former British soldier, continues his quest, venturing into Limbo. In this immaterial place he encounters a fellow traveler only remembered in legends. Once met, Jensen finds that legends aren't necessarily true.

The journey continues for James Jensen, once a soldier in the British Army in the 19th century India and now The Sadhu, a spiritual warrior seeking shelter from the storm that rages in his soul. Somewhere in his journey from limbo into the corporeal world, James seems to be trapped in a place where the distinction between dreams and reality are blurred. This Dreamtime is a manifestation of a collective unconsciousness, where nothing is as it seems. Seeking to rescue a someone he loves from the clutches of the evil Silent Ones, James encounters a being who alters his perception of reality forever. Can James face his own darkest fears and desires, and find a way out of this place before it claims his sanity?

Formerly of the British Army, James Jensen continues his journey as The Sadhu, a spiritual warrior seeking peace from the turbulence of his soul. In his journey from limbo to the real world, James appears to be trapped in a waking dream. It is the manifestation of mans collective unconsciousness and he must struggle through it in an attempt to save his love from the Silent Ones. Insanity threatens if Jensen cannot face his darkest fears and desires to find a way out.

Once he was a soldier for the British Empire. Now, James Jensen is a sadhu, a mystic warrior, and he searches for the son he had believed to be dead. Joining forces with the legendary hermit king of Limbo, Trishanku, James ventures deep into the Central Indian forest to free his son from the clutches of the Silent Ones. But a lost tribe of warriors waits in ambush for James and Trishanku!

James Jensen, mystic warrior, searches for the son he once thought dead. Allied with the legendary hermit king of Limbo, Trishanku, Jensen penetrates the Central Indian forest to free his son from the Silent Ones. The journey is interrupted, however, when they are ambushed by a lost tribe of warriors.

The second Sadhu saga reaches its stunning climax! James Jensen, the British soldier who became a mystic warrior, and his mysterious ally Trishanku launch an all-out attack on the stronghold of the Silent Ones in a desperate effort to save Jensen's son. But even as they breach the outer defenses of the cult's fortress, Jensen and Trishanku realize that the devious Grand Mistress has sprung a trap that might forever change the very fabric of this world and beyond!

Mister Fantastic, Invisible Woman, Human Torch and The Thing: Marvel's First Family has this month's MARVEL SPOTLIGHT all to themselves, with a comprehensive look at the House of Ideas' flagship comic! It was November 1961 when the first issue of Stan Lee and Jack Kirby's innovative new take on super heroes hit the newsstands. Since then, the World's Greatest Comic has gone on strong for more than 540 issues, and dozens of spin-offs and mini-series! Look for interviews with the writers and artists who have worked on the FF, in both the past and the present, along with special features and preview materials. It's 48 pages full of Fantastic Four!

volume.name: Marvel Spotlight: Fantastic Four and Silver Surfer

description: THE FLASH & GREEN LANTERN: THE BRAVE AND THE BOLD explores the unlikely relationship between two men who shared nothing in common but a heroic nature. As the fearless ring-wielding Green Lantern, Hal Jordan was a cocky and brash adventurer who believed himself to be invincible. His polar opposite, Barry Allen was a modest and clean-cut police scientist who respected his own mortality. But in spite of their extreme differences, Green Lantern and the Flash were the best of friends. Featuring appearances by Kid Flash and Green Arrow, this book recounts some of their greatest adventures together and explains how the fastest man alive and the emerald knight put aside their differences and formed an unbreakable bond of friendship.
name: TPB

volume.name: Flash & Green Lantern: The Brave and the Bold

description: Batman and Superman, are hailed as the two greatest super-heroes of all time. This hardcover collection reprints, as they were originally published, the earliest tales of when these two icons first met and fought crime together. Featured in this edition are the memorable tales of the first time Superman and Batman revealed their secret identities to each other, the first time the two heroes traded identities, and the unforgettable story of when Superman lost his powers and Batman mysteriously gained them.
name: Volume 1

description: An alien blessed with incredible powers and a millionaire playboy obsessed with justice, Superman and Batman are two of the most dynamic and intriguing super-heroes of all time. Each fighting crime with his own style and methods, the Dark Knight Detective and the Man of Steel have become legends across the globe. WORLD'S FINEST ARCHIVES VOL. 2 reprints sixteen of their early adventures as partners against crime. Also featuring Robin the Boy Wonder, this book of classics includes fun and exciting tales in which the Dynamic Duo gain incredible powers, the Joker and Lex Luthor form a deadly alliance, and Robin becomes the boss of Batman and Superman.
name: Volume 2

description: Exploding from the panels of the Bullpen Bits comic strip, here come the Mini-Marvels in their very own full- length comedy-packed comic book adventure! When J. Jonah Jameson sends Spidey on an important paperboy mission, the wee wall-crawler better deliver... or else! Guest stars abound in this all-new 28-page funnybook feature story, including Marvel.com's own animated movie-star, Hawkeye! Plus, a collection of the original Bullpen Bits comic strips that started it all! That's 48 pages of Mini-Marvel Mayhem by "Crazy" Chris Giarrusso!
name: Paperboy Blues
